reviewText: If you're even considering looking at this product, you might as well buy it already. The amount of content you get for the price is well worth it. If you are a fan of anyone from SM's family, get this; you won't be disappointed. I'm only really a huge fan of Girls Generation, yet all of the other artists featured in this set give a phenomenal performance, and the documentaries make me earn new respect for some of the artists I wouldn't have otherwise thought twice about. I am very satisfied with this set.

reviewText: I've been listening to KPOP music for a few years now & this was a good find to me. I can't find a lot of concerts for my favorite singers online, so I'm glad I found this. This is an awesome concert & the bonus features are great. I wish I could've gone to this concert for myself.

reviewText: I love kpop as much as the next kpopper, but I expected a lot more. The groups are fantastic, but the editing of the concert wasn't anything great. The audio makes the crowd sound lifeless (I think only the front of the audience was recorded), some songs just HAD to be lip synced, and the camera shots of the audience was questionable (see Side note).But hey, this DVDs has HOURS of kpop goodness, can't go wrong with that. Super Junior really stole the show from the other SM groups. Also, the extras are what you would expect from kpop docs and reality shows: kpop idols acting silly..Side note: I know Kpop is trying to gain popularity in the West, but was it really necessary to cut to all the non-Asian attendees? (I think they cut to the same guy twice..)
summary: I AM...not content, but also not disappointed.
